The files and skripts in here do either
1. create & configure parts of jollix and the jollix system itself.
   Execution is usually done from cvsroot/jollix    (EXTERN)
2. nifty things in the running jollix system, e.g.  
   mounting partitions, setting up the network etc.
   These scripts have a line like "# location in cloop: ..."
   to inidicate the place within the jollix system. (INTERN)

create-cloop	-- creates the compressed loopback archive	(EXTERN)
create-initrd	-- creates the initial ramdisk 			(EXTERN)
create-iso	-- creates the jollix iso			(EXTERN)
csanleg		-- creates desktop icon to play Counter-Strike	(INTERN)
local		-- /etc/init.d/local startup script		(INTERN)
lss16toppm	-- converts lss to ppm 16 bit image		(EXTERN)
modules-jollix	-- loads all possible kernel modules		(INTERN)
ppmtolss16	-- converts ppm to lss 16 bit image		(EXTERN)
settings	-- describes current production environment	(EXTERN)
transitmount	-- mounts hd partitions under /mnt/transit	(INTERN)
x-net-setup	-- sets up a network interface			(INTERN)
x-net-setup-sudo - calls x-net-setup as root			(INTERN) 






